# Performance guardrails

- Don’t do expensive work in render: parsing, sorting, grouping, heavy mapping of 50k+ points.
- Prefer memoization when it prevents real work; avoid “cargo-cult” memoization.
- Keep effect dependencies correct; don’t re-subscribe on every render.
- For large lists/tables, prefer virtualization (you already use `@tanstack/react-virtual`).
- For heavy transforms, use `src/compute/` and/or worker pathways in `src/engine/`.
- When changing chart code, sanity-check: “does this create new arrays/objects every frame?”

